{{- define "wake_immediate_discovery" -}}
Urgent discoveries need immediate action:

1. Read discovered[] entries with urgency=immediate
2. For each, execute decision NOW:
   - Convert to task → execute liza_add_tasks tool NOW, then set converted_to_task=<new-task-id> on the discovery entry (edit state.yaml + liza_validate)
   - Defer → set converted_to_task="deferred" on the discovery entry (edit state.yaml + liza_validate)
   - Dismiss → set converted_to_task="dismissed" on the discovery entry (edit state.yaml + liza_validate)
   NOTE: converted_to_task is the ONLY field you may edit directly — it has no MCP tool yet. Never edit task status or other fields directly.
3. Prioritize new tasks appropriately (may be high priority)
4. Check if discoveries invalidate existing tasks — supersede them if needed
5. All tools must be executed in this session.

Do NOT call liza_sprint_checkpoint. Process all discovered[] entries and exit. If a discovery cannot be resolved, defer it with rationale.
{{- end -}}
